description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Sister/Charge Nurse to provide clinical leadership to our nursing and support staff in the delivery of excellent nursing care within Respiratory Service in Medicine Directorate. Ward 49 is our new 8 bedded High Level Respiratory Unit, where we are able to provide non-invasive ventilation for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and dedicated individual to lead our nursing team. They will have excellent communication skills and have the ability, drive and enthusiasm to motivate and drive an enthusiastic team to provide high quality patient care and experience. You will need to have excellent organisational and interpersonal skills, the ability to demonstrate leadership and a sound understanding of respiratory and general medical nursing. Please be aware this will include caring for covid patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be supported in their role by the Matron for the ward area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma McColl&lt;/p&gt;
